examples.en: He had respect for his rivals.
The teams have been longtime rivals.
He finished 39 seconds ahead of his main rival.
She has no rivals as a female rock singer.
He was a spy planted in the office by a rival company.
I had no idea of rivalling him or his poems.
Of all the flowers in the garden few can rival the lily.
We are rivaling for first place in the race.
I'd get a scoop to rival Watergate.
To checkmate their dangerous rival instantly.
Halifax in fertility of thought had no rival.
There was a violent confrontation between rival supporters after the match.
Nothing can rival cotton for durability.
They still remain bitter rivals (=hate each other).
His nearest rival announced he would not contest a run-off.
The newest model has several advantages over its rivals.
He succeeded to jump higher than his rival at the first try.
The police try to keep rival supporters apart at all matches.
He impugned his rival's character.
He was shot by a member of a rival gang.
To head my rival off I indulged in a tremendous flirtation.
The politician clawed his rival.
The college's facilities rival those of Harvard and Yale.
There's not another guitarist to rival the sheer physicality of his work.
The main rival to his pneumonia was the prolific thrush which went into his throat and stomach.
The embattled entrepreneur struck a deal with a rival businessman in an attempt to save his teetering business empire.
A rival company topped our offer by $5 million.
She was 2 minutes faster than her nearest rival.
Maisie looked her rival up and down with a critical eye.
He spewed venom against his rival.
